				"id": "ALAS2KERNEL-5.4-2024-088",
				"title": "Amazon Linux 2 - Kernel-5.4 2.0 - ALAS2KERNEL-5.4-2024-088: medium priority package update for kernel",
				"description": "Package updates are available for Amazon Linux 2 - Kernel-5.4 that fix the following vulnerabilities:\nCVE-2024-49996:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ncifs: Fix buffer overflow when parsing NFS reparse points\n\nCVE-2024-47685:\n\tsyzbot reported that nf_reject_ip6_tcphdr_put() was possibly sending garbage on the four reserved tcp bits (th->res1)\n\nUse skb_put_zero() to clear the whole TCP header, as done in nf_reject_ip_tcphdr_put()\n\nCVE-2024-38538:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet: bridge: xmit: make sure we have at least eth header len bytes\n\nCVE-2024-26921:\n\tIn the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ninet: inet_defrag: prevent sk release while still in use\n",
